    [name] => STEAMPUNK SUBMARINE (PRIVATE GAME ONLY)
    [description] => <p><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-family: 'arial black', 'avant garde'; font-size: large;">Players: 2-8&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-family: 'arial black', 'avant garde'; font-size: large;">Difficulty: Intermediate</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-family: 'arial black', 'avant garde'; font-size: large;">Success Rate: 42%</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-family: 'arial black', 'avant garde'; font-size: large;">Price: $40/Player ($45/player for a group of 2)</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-size: medium;">You are a crew of specialist engineers, who have recently been hired to perform maintenance on this mysterious and ancient submarine. The story is that she has been running for many years, needing no fuel and moving almost as though alive. The captain claims that over the past several months, this vessel has slowed down significantly, and this is where you (the repair crew) come in. However, the original engineer who built this technical marvel is long gone, and you don&rsquo;t fully understand how or why this submarine works yet. During this trip, the submarine has started to act up, and many of the systems have shut down, locking you in! She&rsquo;s sinking fast, and if you don&rsquo;t fix the systems and get her running again within 60 minutes, you may never see the sun again. Fix up this submarine and get her home!</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-size: medium;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="color: #c0c0c0; font-size: medium;">Steampunk Submarine is a multi-room experience with an exploratory feel. It gives players an unfolding adventure as they move through each system of the submarine. Are you ready to SUBmerse yourselves in this exciting room?</span></p>
